<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8307179>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Flower diversity in Pauridia. A, P. trifurcillata; B, P. umbraticola; C, P. pusilla; D, P. longituba; E, P. linearis; F, P. gracilipes subsp. speciosa; G, P. curculigoides; H, P. monophylla; I, P.capensis; J, P. canaliculata; K, P. alticola. Photographs by J.C. Paterson-Jones." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8307179/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8307259>
    dc:description "FIGURE 42. Pauridia alticola. A, whole plant; B, flower in longitudinal section; C, stamen in lateral views; D, style and stigma branches; E, ovary in transverse section; F, seed. Scale bar A, B = 20 mm. Scale bar C, D = 6 mm; E = 3 mm; F = 0.7 mm. Drawn by Tracey Nowell [A–E from Thompson 2345 (NBG!); F from Burtt (2000: Fig. 2C)]." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8307259/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8307261>
    dc:description "FIGURE 43 Distribution map for Pauridiaalticola (dots) from Northern and Western Cape, South Africa and P. verna (squares) from Lesotho and KwaZulu-Natal and Eastern Cape, South Africa." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8307261/files/figure.png" ;
